headlines.description: — Collin Sexton scored 30 points, Lauri Markkanen had 27 points and 14 rebounds and the Utah Jazz beat the Detroit Pistons 126-119 on Thursday night for for their second victory in 10 games.
headlines.shortLinkText: Collin Sexton and Keyonte George lead Jazz past Pistons, 126-119

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Orlando Magic

headlines.description: — Shai Gilgeous-Alexander scored 35 points and Jalen Williams scored six straight points in a run in the fourth quarter that helped turned back an Orlando comeback bid as the Oklahoma City Thunder beat the Magic 105-99 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Thunder hold off Orlando's comeback bid, beat the Magic 105-99 behind Gilgeous-Alexander, Williams

headlines.description: — Jordan Poole scored 27 points and Malcolm Brogdon added 25 in his return from injury as the Washington Wizards beat the Charlotte Hornets 123-114 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jordan Poole, Malcolm Brogdon help Wizards snap 3-game skid with a 123-114 win over the Hornets

headlines.description: — Zach LaVine scored a season-high 36 points and the Chicago Bulls used a fourth-quarter flurry to hold off the Boston Celtics 117-108 on Thursday night in the opener of a home-and-home set.
headlines.shortLinkText: Zach LaVine scores season-high 36 points to help the Bulls hold off the Celtics 117-108

headlines.description: — Cam Johnson hit a tiebreaking 3-pointer with less than two minutes remaining in the fourth quarter and finished with 33 points as the Brooklyn Nets overcame a 10-point deficit and beat the Toronto Raptors 101-94 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Johnson hits tiebreaking 3, scores 15 of his 33 points in the 4th as Nets rally to beat Raptors

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Houston Rockets

headlines.description: — Jalen Green scored 34 points to lead the Houston Rockets to a 133-113 win over the New Orleans Pelicans on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jalen Green and Rockets beat New Orleans 133-113 and send Pelicans to their 5th straight loss

events.name: Golden State Warriors at Memphis Grizzlies

headlines.description: — Santi Aldama had 21 points and 14 rebounds, and the Memphis Grizzlies set a franchise record with 27 3-pointers in a 144-93 victory over the Golden State Warriors on Thursday night, the biggest win in the NBA this season.
headlines.shortLinkText: Grizzlies make franchise-record 27 3s and rout Warriors 144-93, biggest win in NBA this season

events.name: Atlanta Hawks at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — Norman Powell scored 29 points, James Harden added 24 and Ivica Zubac had 21 points and 15 rebounds as the Los Angeles Clippers beat Dallas 118-95 on Thursday night in the Mavericks’ first game this season playing <a...
headlines.shortLinkText: Clippers beat Dallas 118-95 as Mavericks' star guards Doncic and Irving sit due to injury

headlines.description: — Pascal Siakam had 25 points and 18 rebounds, Myles Turner added 19 points and the Indiana Pacers beat the Phoenix Suns 120-111 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Siakam has 25 points and 18 rebounds to lead the Pacers past the Suns, 120-111

events.name: New York Knicks at Minnesota Timberwolves

headlines.description: — Karl-Anthony Towns had 32 points and 20 rebounds in his return to Minnesota, leading the inspired New York Knicks past the Timberwolves...
headlines.shortLinkText: Towns tears up T-wolves in return with 32 points and 20 rebounds in 133-107 romp by Knicks

events.name: Denver Nuggets at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Anfernee Simons made a driving layup at the buzzer to give the Portland Trail Blazers a 122-120 victory over Nikola Jokic and the Denver Nuggets on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Simons' buzzer-beating layup gives the Blazers a 122-120 win over the Nuggets

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Sacramento Kings

headlines.description: — LeBron James had 19 points, six rebounds and seven assists while breaking the NBA record for regular-season minutes, helping the Los Angeles beat the Sacramento Kings 113-100 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Another record for LeBron James in the Lakers' 113-100 victory over the Kings
